// Semantic direction:
// kvantisering_inferens reduces numerical precision to accelerate inference.
// kv_per_gruppe applies different scales to groups of weights (e.g., 128 elements).
// ptq_kalibrering collects activation statistics to determine optimal scale/zero_point.
// gptq quantizes weights by solving a layer-wise quantization problem with Hessian information.
// awq_kvant (Activation-aware Weight Quantization) finds channels important to activations.
// strukturert_sparsitet prunes entire heads, channels, or attention patterns for hardware speedup.
// lotteri_hypotese: dense networks contain sparse sub-networks trainable in isolation.
// mixture_of_experts routes each token to moe_top_k experts, enabling massive capacity.
// moe_kapasitetsfaktor limits how many tokens each expert processes to prevent overload.
// kd_temperatur softens probability distributions: p_i = exp(z_i/T) / Σexp(z_j/T).
// kd_myke_etiketter transfer knowledge from teacher logits rather than just hard labels.
// torch_compile traces and fuses operations into optimized GPU kernels.
// triton_kernel is a Python-like language for writing custom GPU kernels.
// spekulativ_dekoding uses a small utkastmodell to draft tokens; mål_modell_spec verifies them.
// spec_aksept_rate is the fraction of draft tokens accepted; determines actual speedup.
// medusa_hoder add parallel prediction heads to the main model for self-speculation.
// kontinuerlig_batching replaces requests in a batch as they finish, maximizing GPU utilization.
// chunked_prefill processes long prompts in chunks to overlap with decoding of other requests.
// paged_kv_cache manages KV cache with non-contiguous pages like OS virtual memory.

// Primitive flow:
// GPTQ kvantisering: for hvert lag W: kvantisér kolonne for kolonne
//   for kolonne i: w_q = round(w/skala) * skala -> feil = w - w_q
//   oppdater resterende kolonner via Hessian: W[:,j+1:] -= w_q_err * H_inv[i,j+1:]
// Spekulativ dekoding: utkastmodell generer K tokens med sannsynligheter q(x)
//   mål_modell kjør parallelt på K+1 tokens -> sannsynligheter p(x)
//   godta token i: if u ~ U[0,1] < min(1, p(x_i)/q(x_i)) -> akseptert
//   ellers: sample ny token fra normalisert (p-q) fordeling
// Continuous batching: iterasjonsnivå_planlegging per dekodingssteg
//   fullførte sekvenser: fjern fra batch umiddelbart
//   nye forespørsler: sett inn i ledig plass -> dynamisk batch-størrelse

// This defines efficient inference: GPTQ/AWQ quantization, structured sparsity, Mixture of
// Experts routing, knowledge distillation, model compilation (Triton/TensorRT), speculative
// decoding with draft models and Medusa heads, continuous batching, and paged KV cache.
